sub_topic: Prove that the symmetric difference of two sets is not distributive over complement.
message_1: Let A = {3, 5, 7} and B = {5, 7, 9}. Find the symmetric difference of the sets A and B, and then find the complement of the symmetric difference. Finally, show that the symmetric difference of complement of A and complement of B is not equal to the complement of the symmetric difference of A and B.
